Untitled Document  Dr  Mitra Dutta  Professor and Head  r n         r n        Electrical and Computer Engineering Department r n         r n      University of Illinois at Chicago   r n              S  Morgan St M C            r n           r n          Chicago  IL             r n           r n          Email dutta ece uic edu       r n           r n          Tel              r n          Fax               r n           r n       Mitra Dutta  is currently a UIC Distinguished Professor and the Head of the Electrical and Computer Engineering Department at the University of Illinois at Chicago  Her research has focused on electronic and optoelectronic devices as well as the physics of these materials and device structures  After her Ph D  from University of Cincinnati        and postdoctoral appointments at Purdue University             City College of New York             and Visiting Researcher at Brookhaven National Laboratory             Dr  Dutta joined the US Army Research Laboratory  then called Electronics Technology and Devices Laboratory   ETDL  first as Team Leader of the Optoelectronics Team  then as Branch Chief and finally as Division Director of the Physics Division supervising and managing a large group of scientists and engineers  In      she moved to the US Army Research Office  ARO  where after a short time as a program manager for quantum electronics  she ran the Electronics Division In      she was promoted to the Senior Executive Service as Director of the Research Technology and Integration Directorate  having oversight over the     M ARO budget  Dr  Dutta has held adjunct professor positions at Rutgers University  University of Maryland  North Carolina State University  and University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill  She has authored or co authored over     publications and presentations  holds    US and Canadian patents  has co edited five books and is a co author on a sixth  She served on the Army Science and Technology committee for Homeland Security  and coauthored the NRC Reports   and   for the Board for Army Science and Technology   Honors and Awards    Current PhD Students   PhD Students Graduated from UIC   Institutional and Professional Service  Last   Years    Examples from last   years follow   Other Items 